subSubSection.paragraph:
Note. –
One specimen (
Gautier 5790
) collected with flower buds in the same forest, but at higher altitude (
670 m
) on an exposed ridge on the eastern summit of Ivohibe Peak, is clearly a member of the same genus. The tree was smaller in size (
7 m
) and had smaller leaves. It was first thought to be merely an individual adapted to a more exposed site, but molecular analysis indicates that it is also genetically different from the 
type
population. Until more fertile material is collected from this population we refrain from including it in the new species.
